# (''mainly US'') A name for the hash or square symbol ('''#'''), used mainly in telephony and computing
#*'''2004''': Strings are enclosed in double quotation marks, numbers are not enclosed in anything, and dates and Boolean values are enclosed between '''octothorpe''' (#) characters. — Andrew Pitonyak, ''Openoffice.Org Macros Explained'' (Hentzenwerke 2004, p. 139)

